I chaired today at Mohammed VI Polytechnic University in Rabat  the opening ceremony of the  Morocco-Estonia E-Connect  forum on E-Gov  along with Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Estonia  Mr. Margus Tsahkna.  This forum aims to serve as a bridge for the exchange of experiences between the Kingdom of Morocco and the Republic of Estonia in areas related to E-Gov and digital governance  thus strengthening the digital transformation of our country in line with the national strategy  Digital Morocco 2030   which has received the gracious endorsement of His Majesty the King Mohammed VI  may God assist Him.  In my speech on the occasion  I recalled the various initiatives taking place in our country in the digital field  highlighting the priority our country gives to digitization as a real lever for change and development. I also stressed the need to exchange experiences with the Republic of Estonia  pioneer in the field of E-Gov services  and learn about the best practices. #DigitalMorocco2030 #Ø§Ù„Ù…ØºØ±Ø¨_Ø§Ù„Ø±Ù‚Ù…ÙŠ_2030 #Egov #MTNRA #Morocco

Earlier this week  I held a work meeting with VISA Senior Vice President & Group Country Manager for North Africa  Levant and Pakistan  Ms. Leila Serhan  along with her team. The meeting took place on the sidelines of my participation in GITEX GLOBAL  the world s tech and startups event  in Dubai-UAE.  The meeting focused on ways to strengthen the partnership with Visa  especially in areas related to startups and fintech  as well as prospects for cooperation in various related fields. On this occasion  I shed light on the most important axes of the national strategy  Digital Morocco 2030   which aims  among other goals  to boost the digital economy and to establish the Kingdom as a digitally productive country. I participated today in the Africa Trade & Invest Forum: Managing Risk  organized by the Afrika-Verein der deutschen Wirtschaft (German - African Business Association) in Frankfurt  Germany.  During the opening discussion  we explored Africa s role as a trade and investment partner amidst geopolitical shifts. We examined the investment opportunities the continent offers and its growing role as an economic and trade partner. We also discussed the impact of external risk perceptions on local growth  the potential for redefining value and supply chains  and how European-African collaboration can help mitigate risks and boost foreign direct investment in Africa.

text: The iconic @youssra shared heartfelt words of gratitude and joy moments after being honored with the prestigious Omar Sharif Award at the #EnigmaMagazine x @GoldenGlobes Tribute Event!  History was made as Enigma Magazine partnered with the prestigious Golden Globes from Hollywood to host a spectacular tribute event honoring the rich legacy of Arab cinema and television in Cairo  Egypt.  The evening celebrated two legendary icons of Egyptian cinema and television  @hussien.fahmi.official and @youssra  who were honored with the inaugural Omar Sharif Award.  The star-studded red carpet gala was a glamorous night filled with groundbreaking  heartfelt  and unforgettable moments of appreciation and celebration. I participated today in the Africa Trade & Invest Forum: Managing Risk  organized by the Afrika-Verein (German-African Business Association) in Frankfurt  Germany.  During the opening discussion  we explored Africa s role as a trade and investment partner amidst geopolitical shifts. We examined the investment opportunities the continent offers and its growing role as an economic and trade partner. We also discussed the impact of external risk perceptions on local growth  the potential for redefining value and supply chains  and how European-African collaboration can help mitigate risks and boost foreign direct investment in Africa.
